		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Phila</placeName> <date>April 11th 1867</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Mr. A. Hart</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><sic>Alow</sic> me to trouble you again for my<lb/> friend. <persName>Dr. Morris Coster</persName> in <placeName>N. Y. City</placeName>&#44; for the pur<lb/> pose to know if <persName>Dr. S. Mulder&#39;s</persName> Bible from<lb/> <placeName>Amsterdam</placeName> &#40;<placeName>Europe</placeName>&#41; &#8220;Bybel voor de Israeli<lb/>tische jeuzd&#8221; has been translated from the Dutch<lb/> into the English language by certain &#8220;<hi rend="underline"><persName>Peres</persName></hi>&#8221; and<lb/> if <hi rend="underline"><persName>Rev. Leeser</persName></hi> has been the editor&#63; That is<lb/> what my friend wrote me this morning to inquire<lb/> after.</p>
				<p>In thanking you very much for your trouble<lb/> I hope to be forwarded with your kind reply and<lb/> in the meantime I have the honor to be<lb/> most respectfully. Yours obediently</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">E. Lione Dz</persName></p>
				<p>My Address is&#58;</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Mr E. Lione Dz</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>230 South Eight Strt Phila</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="Page 2&#44; attached"></p>
				<p>On <date>Sunday</date> next Dr.<add>&#63;</add> at noon&#44; the ceremony of receiving<lb/> the Divine Covenant of <persName>Abraham</persName> will be performed on a young man<lb/> of 19 years. The romance is interesting &#38;  as  I have heard<lb/> it from his own lips send this version. About 35 years ago<lb/> a great migration of Jews took place from <placeName>Salonica</placeName> to <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName>&#58; a<lb/> party of the pilgrims were captured by the Greeks &#38;  carried to <placeName><sic>Beyrout</sic></placeName><lb/> and sold as slaves &#8212; among whom was a woman with a female<lb/>  child at her breast&#58; at the age of 14 this child was betrothed to the<lb/> purchaser &#38;  in due time bore him a son &#40;the hero of this tale&#41;<lb/> and two daughters still in a convent. The boy was educated in<lb/> the missionary college &#38;  appears very talented&#58; speaks several languages<lb/> &#40;English is one&#41; within the last 2 years his parents died &#38;  the grandmother<lb/> who ever adhered to her faith has managed to steal him away<lb/> &#38;  having with the aid of others instilled into him a knowledge of<lb/> the religion of his ancestors he has resolved on embracing it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In <placeName>England</placeName> they declined admitted him or &#39;twas contrary<lb/> to the Charter &#38;  meeting <persName>Rabbi Yechida Cohen</persName> he advised<lb/> them to proceed to the <placeName>States</placeName> where any &#38;  every thing<lb/> can be done. His Grandmother&#44; a male courier &#38;  himself wear<lb/> the Persian dress. <persName>Sir Abraham</persName> is <add>Hebrew</add>&#58;</p>
				<p>There is also here a <add>Hebrew</add> from <add>Hebrew</add> who states that<lb/> there are upwards of 24 thousand Jews there &#38;  they are now<lb/> suffering from a persecution similar to that of<lb/> <placeName>Damascus</placeName>. I have not seen his paper &#8212; he is now sick<lb/> but <persName>B<add>&#63;</add></persName> has <sic>shewn</sic> me a letter he rec&#39;d from <persName>Revd<lb/> D. Meldola</persName> on his a&#47;c.  It is feared he will lay his bones<lb/> here. This is a brief outline but I believe is substan<lb/>tially correct. Excuse writing.  <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">A J M<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
		</body>
